==Book and film==
I've replaced the original book infobox information removed without explanation by an editor with a score of Wiki edits, half of which were about this subject.[http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=The_Rape_of_Europa&action=historysubmit&diff=178590018&oldid=177975039]

No explanation was given, but possibly COI was involved. The book is an extensive scholarly reference. The movie is a popularization that spends considerable time explaining who the Nazi's were, dwelling on their pictures, and interviewing a particular person at length who has an ownership dispute with Austrian museums. The movie possibly suggests [[WP:BIAS]].

I'm unclear whether both infoboxes are appropriate, if not, then the original, scholarly, award-winning book should be retained, not the money-losing non-award-winning film.

